<title>DENMARK: Danish takeover target Phoenix sells unit.</title>
<headline>Danish takeover target Phoenix sells unit.</headline>
<dateline>COPENHAGEN 1997-02-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>Danish roadbuilder Phoenix Contractors -- the object of takeover bids by three companies -- has sold its Nordisk Triclair unit to the FLS group's Unicon Beton, the buyer said on Friday.</p>
<p>News of the sale was announced just before the Copenhagen Stock Exchange closed, with the Phoenix C-share up 5.66 crowns to 660.66, well above the highest offer so far of 650 crowns per share from Norwegian suitor Rieber and Son.</p>
<p>Other offers were of 625 crowns per share from building contractor Marius Pedersen and 600 crowns from heavyweight construction and chemicals group Superfos.</p>
